description.narrative: UNICEF effectively leveraged its engagement with public sector donors and raised approximately US$ 17 million in new funds; with around US$ 5 million of additional funds in the firm pipeline for 2022. The office also continued the development and operationalization of its strategy for private sector engagement, with key milestones including the signing of formal agreements with two Libyan private sector entities. UNICEF continued to invest in advocacy around key areas of concern, including COVID-19 prevention and control measures, climate change, and the protection of children from violence, including the most vulnerable such as refugee and migrant children.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:16/01/2022
